{
  "texts": [
    "The PointNet is used to supplement the lack of information in high resolution single point mode.",
    "Thus, rapid perception and collection of point cloud features can be realized in large-scale scenarios.",
    "The newly proposed SPVNAS structure (Liu et al., 2019b) further improves PC-Conv.",
    "By combining with sparse convolution structure, it can accommodate voxel lattice with higher resolution and improve the computing efficiency of the network.",
    "At the same time, because some existing models are not end-to-end, combining traditional registration methods is necessary."
  ]
}